messages.content: What is the main purpose of sd-ppp?
sd-ppp is a tool that integrates Stable Diffusion with Adobe Photoshop, allowing users to generate and manipulate images using ComfyUI nodes and various features.
Which version of sd-ppp added support for sending images to the boundary?
Support for sending images to the boundary was added in version 1.3.0 of sd-ppp, released on 2024-08-24.
What new ComfyUI nodes were introduced in sd-ppp version 1.3.0?
In version 1.3.0 of sd-ppp, the following new ComfyUI nodes were introduced: GetTextFromLayer, GetDocument, GetLayerByID, GetLinkedLayer, GetLayersInGroup, and ParseLayerInfo.
When did sd-ppp become compatible with the latest ComfyUI (August version)?
sd-ppp became compatible with the latest ComfyUI (August version) in the release of version 1.2.2 on 2024-08-18.
In which version of sd-ppp was the .ccx download button added to the Comfy node and webui's setting popup?
The .ccx download button was added to the Comfy node and webui's setting popup in version 1.2.1 of sd-ppp, released on 2024-08-15.
When did sd-ppp start supporting multi-document functionality?
Multi-document support was introduced in version 1.2.0 of sd-ppp, released on 2024-07-30.
Which version of sd-ppp added the generate button and auto-generate checkbox in Photoshop?
The generate button and auto-generate checkbox in Photoshop were added in version 1.2.0 of sd-ppp, released on 2024-07-30.

What is the main purpose of the sd-ppp extension?
The sd-ppp extension is mainly focused on getting and sending elements from and to Photoshop in ComfyUI or Stable Diffusion. It allows Photoshop to become the workspace for SD/ComfyUI.
What are the three main functionalities of sd-ppp?

The three main functionalities of sd-ppp are: 1) getting any layer of any document in any area and amount from Photoshop, 2) sending images to Photoshop to any document/layer/area, and 3) getting text layer's content as prompt.
How can you install the sd-ppp extension in ComfyUI?
You can install the sd-ppp extension in ComfyUI by using ComfyManager to install it or by cloning the repository into your ComfyUI's custom_nodes directory.
What are the two methods to install the Photoshop plugin for sd-ppp?
The two methods to install the Photoshop plugin for sd-ppp are: 1) by using the CCX file, and 2) by using the UXP develop tool.
How can you connect to Stable Diffusion in Photoshop when using sd-ppp?
You can connect to Stable Diffusion in Photoshop by using the sd-ppp panel in Photoshop and filling in the correct URL and port number.
What is the minimum version of Photoshop required to use sd-ppp?
The minimum version of Photoshop required to use sd-ppp is Photoshop 24.4.0.
What are some of the showcase examples of using sd-ppp with ComfyUI?
Some of the showcase examples of using sd-ppp with ComfyUI include: regional prompting, live-painting, controlnet, and IC-light.
